  <prompt>
    Fix Bug 3 from operator smoke feedback: the "Create new workspace" popup in
    SpaarkeAi's WorkspacePaneMenu is empty because the `sprk_workspacelayoutwizard`
    web resource was not redeployed by task 070 (which only deployed `sprk_spaarkeai`).
    Build + redeploy the wizard's web resource so the task 032/033 templateFilter
    URL-param-parsing reaches Dataverse, AND add this wizard to
    `scripts/Deploy-WizardCodePages.ps1` so future deploys cover it automatically.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke deployment operator comfortable with Vite Code Page build, Dataverse web
    resource deployment, and small PowerShell script edits. Verifies the wizard renders
    after deploy via manual click in Power Apps.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_workspacelayoutwizard` is updated in `https://spaarkedev1.crm.dynamics.com` with
    the latest build (includes task 032/033 changes); Power Apps "Create new workspace"
    popup renders the wizard with the 6-template subset; `scripts/Deploy-WizardCodePages.ps1`
    now includes this wizard for future deploys.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 070's deploy memo confirms only two artifacts were deployed: BFF API and
      `sprk_spaarkeai` web resource. The WorkspaceLayoutWizard is a SEPARATE web resource
      (`sprk_workspacelayoutwizard`) deployed by a different solution. Diagnostic agents
      confirmed:
      - Source code at `src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/src/main.tsx` correctly parses
        the `templateFilter` URL query param (task 032's change).
      - Source code at `App.tsx` correctly accepts the `templateFilter` prop (task 033's
        change).
      - Local build artifact at `src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/dist/sprk_workspacelayoutwizard.html`
        already includes these changes (built today).
      - `scripts/Deploy-WizardCodePages.ps1` does NOT include `sprk_workspacelayoutwizard`
        in its `$webResources` array (omitted from the wizard list).

      Two fixes needed:
      1. Deploy the existing local build to Dataverse.
      2. Add the wizard to `Deploy-WizardCodePages.ps1` for durability.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/dist/sprk_workspacelayoutwizard.html</file>
